Method behavioural requirements:
- The integer array parameter `balls` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `balls` must have a length between 1 and 8.
- Each element in the integer array parameter `balls` must be between 1 and 6.
- The sum of all elements in the integer array parameter `balls` must be even.
- The double result is the probability that the two boxes have the same number of distinct balls after shuffling uniformly at random.